{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LVTJHSAR4THiYB6yzBReYV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GaMdELGmU7U8bC6tXEpTmX","name":"Agent","input":{"subagent_type":"Explore","description":"Inventory backend closecall code","prompt":"Thoroughly inventory the Close Call backend code. Search in `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/`. I need:\n\n1. Account decoders — grep for \"CloseCall\" or \"closecall\" in `worker/account-decoder.ts` — list interfaces and functions with file:line\n2. Settlement tx builders — grep for \"CloseCall\" or \"closecall\" in `worker/settle-tx.ts` — list functions with file:line\n3. Clock worker — read `worker/closecall-clock.ts` if it exists — list exports and key functions with file:line\n4. Database — grep for \"closecall\" in `db.ts` — list tables, queries, types with file:line\n5. API routes — check `routes/closecall.ts` if it exists — list routes with file:line\n6. Rounds endpoint — grep for \"closecall\" in `routes/rounds.ts` — show how it handles closecall rounds\n7. Config — grep for \"pyth\" or \"closecall\" in `config.ts`\n8. Index.ts — grep for \"closecall\" to see how it's wired up\n9. Migration files — check `migrations/` for closecall-related SQL\n\nFor each item, provide exact file:line references. Be thorough."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24236,"cache_read_input_tokens":27195,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24236},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"efe120e9-7ceb-4e75-b227-230da807bdef","uuid":"eae8e5de-01be-4241-af8c-3a77431c3658"}
