{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GaMdELGmU7U8bC6tXEpTmX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive inventory:\n\n## Close Call Backend Code Inventory\n\n### 1. Account Decoders — `worker/account-decoder.ts`\n\n**Interfaces** (Close Call-specific):\n- `DecodedCloseCallRound` (line 125-142): Decodes on-chain CloseCallRound account with roundId, server, phase, green/red entries, pools, prices, fees\n- `DecodedCloseCallConfig` (line 144-152): Decodes CloseCallConfig with authority, treasury, pythFeedId, bettingWindowSecs, maxEntriesPerSide, paused\n\n**Functions** (Close Call):\n- `decodeCloseCallRound(data: Buffer)` (line 239-259): Returns DecodedCloseCallRound from buffer\n- `decodeCloseCallConfig(data: Buffer)` (line 261-272): Returns DecodedCloseCallConfig from buffer\n- `closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter()` (line 293-297): Returns memcmp filter for CloseCallRound account discovery\n\n**Helper enum converters** (used by decoders):\n- `closeCallPhaseToNumber(phase)` (line 50-55): Converts phase enum (Open=0, Settled=1, Refunded=2)\n- `outcomeToNumber(outcome)` (line 58-64): Converts outcome enum (Pending=0, Green=1, Red=2, Refund=3)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Settlement TX Builders — `worker/settle-tx.ts`\n\n**Instruction discriminators** (from Close Call IDL):\n- `CC_CREATE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR` (line 51)\n- `CC_SETTLE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR` (line 52)\n- `CC_TIMEOUT_REFUND_DISCRIMINATOR` (line 53)\n\n**PDA derivers**:\n- `deriveCloseCallConfigPda()` (line 524-529): Seeds: [\"closecall_config\"]\n- `deriveCloseCallRoundPda(roundId)` (line 531-536): Seeds: [\"cc_round\", roundId]\n\n**Close Call TX builders**:\n- `buildCloseCallCreateRoundTx(deps, roundId, pythPriceAccount)` (line 554-583): Builds + signs create_round instruction\n  - Keys: server (signer, writable), config (read), round (init), price_update (read), system_program\n  - Data: CC_CREATE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR + roundId (16 bytes total)\n  - Returns: {tx, roundPda}\n\n- `buildCloseCallSettleRoundTx(deps, roundId, pythPriceAccount, treasury, winnerAccounts)` (line 591-626): Builds settle_round instruction\n  - Keys: caller (signer, writable), round (writable), config, price_update, treasury, rent_receiver, ...winnerAccounts\n  - Data: CC_SETTLE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR + roundId\n  - Supports auto-payout to winners via remaining accounts\n\n- `buildCloseCallTimeoutRefundTx(deps, roundId, playerAccounts)` (line 634-665): Builds timeout_refund instruction (permissionless)\n  - Keys: caller (signer, writable), round (writable), config, rent_receiver, ...playerAccounts\n  - Refunds all players after resolve deadline\n\n**Types**:\n- `CloseCallTxDeps` (line 543-546): connection, serverKeypair\n- `CloseCallPhase` mapping: \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\"\n- `CloseCallOutcome` mapping: \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\"\n\n**Error classes**:\n- `PermanentSettleError` (line 672-677)\n- `TransientSettleError` (line 681-686)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Close Call Clock Worker — `worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n\n**Exports**:\n- `createCloseCallClockWorker(deps)` (line 70-422): Factory returning CloseCallClockWorker interface\n  \n**CloseCallClockWorker interface** (line 58-64):\n- `start()`: Discovers existing round, schedules first tick\n- `stop()`: Stops the loop\n- `isRunning`: Getter for running state\n- `tick()`: Public method for testing (runs settle + create)\n\n**Key constants**:\n- `PHASE_OPEN = 0` (line 38)\n- `TICK_OFFSET_MS = 2_000` (line 41): Runs 2s after minute boundary\n- `MAX_TX_RETRIES = 3` (line 44)\n- `TX_RETRY_DELAY_MS = 2_000` (line 45)\n\n**Pyth PriceUpdateV2 raw offsets**:\n- `PYTH_PRICE_OFFSET = 73` (line 33)\n- `PYTH_EXPO_OFFSET = 89` (line 34)\n- `PYTH_MIN_DATA_LEN = 93` (line 35)\n\n**Internal tick logic**:\n- `settlePreviousRound()` (line 198-308): Settlement flow with outcome pre-determination\n  - Determines refund condition: empty entries, one-sided, single player, or equal price\n  - Selects winner accounts based on price comparison\n  - Calls `buildCloseCallSettleRoundTx` with appropriate winner list\n  - Logs settle attempts with retry on failure\n\n- `createNewRound()` (line 314-340): Creates new round at minute boundary\n  - Generates random 8-byte roundId\n  - Calls `buildCloseCallCreateRoundTx`\n  - Updates in-memory active round tracking\n\n- `tick()` (line 346-357): Main loop operation\n  - Step 1: Settle previous round\n  - Step 2: Create new round\n\n- `discoverActiveRound()` (line 157-188): On startup, scans for existing Open round owned by server\n  - Uses `closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter()` to find rounds\n  - Recovers in-memory state from on-chain account\n\n---\n\n### 4. Database — `db.ts`\n\n**Types** (Close Call-specific):\n- `CloseCallPhase = \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\"` (line 16)\n- `CloseCallOutcome = \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\"` (line 17)\n- `CloseCallRound` interface (line 19-36): round_id, pda, server_key, phase, open_price, open_price_expo, close_price, outcome, green_pool, red_pool, total_fee, green_entries, red_entries, settle_tx, created_at, settled_at\n- `InsertCloseCallRoundParams` (line 38-44): roundId, pda, serverKey, openPrice, openPriceExpo\n\n**Db interface methods** (Close Call):\n- `insertCloseCallRound(params)` (line 171): Returns CloseCallRound\n- `getCloseCallRound(roundId)` (line 174): By 16-char hex roundId\n- `getCloseCallCurrentRound()` (line 177): Returns current open round or undefined\n- `getCloseCallHistory(limit)` (line 180): Returns last N settled/refunded rounds\n- `settleCloseCallRound(roundId, updates)` (line 183-196): Updates phase, outcome, closePrice, pools, fees, entries, settleTx\n\n**Implementation** (createDb):\n- `insertCloseCallRound` (line 353-366): INSERT into closecall_rounds table\n- `getCloseCallRound` (line 368-373): SELECT by round_id\n- `getCloseCallCurrentRound` (line 375-383): SELECT WHERE phase='open' ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 1\n- `getCloseCallHistory` (line 385-393): SELECT WHERE phase IN ('settled','refunded') ORDER BY settled_at DESC\n- `settleCloseCallRound` (line 395-415): UPDATE closecall_rounds with settlement data\n\n**Normalizer** (internal):\n- `normalizeCloseCallRound(row)` (line 202-219): Converts BIGINT→Number, parses JSONB entries\n\n---\n\n### 5. API Routes — `routes/closecall.ts`\n\n**Routes**:\n- `GET /closecall/current-round` (line 43-49): Returns active round + pool state\n  - Response: `{round: null | formatCloseCallRound(round)}`\n  \n- `GET /closecall/history` (line 51-56): Last N settled/refunded rounds\n  - Query param: `limit` (1-100, default 20)\n  - Response: `{rounds: [formatCloseCallRound(...)]}`\n\n**Response formatter** (line 15-37):\n- `formatCloseCallRound(round)`: Returns camelCase object with:\n  - roundId, pda, phase, openPrice, openPriceExpo, closePrice, outcome\n  - greenPool, redPool, totalPool (calculated), totalFee\n  - greenEntries, redEntries, greenCount, redCount\n  - settleTx, createdAt, settledAt (ISO strings)\n\n---\n\n### 6. Rounds Endpoint (Unified) — `routes/rounds.ts`\n\n**Routes**:\n- `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` (line 131-152): Unified endpoint for all game types\n  - Validates matchId is 16-char hex\n  - Tries commit-reveal `rounds` table first\n  - Falls back to `closecall_rounds` table\n  - Returns game-specific formatted response\n  - Response: `formatRoundResponse()` or `formatCloseCallResponse()`\n\n- `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` (line 154-163): By PDA (commit-reveal games only)\n\n**Close Call formatter** (line 85-124):\n- `formatCloseCallResponse(round)`: Returns camelCase with:\n  - pda, game: \"closecall\", phase, matchId (from round_id)\n  - Pool data: openPrice, openPriceExpo, greenPool, redPool, totalPool, greenCount, redCount\n  - Entries: greenEntries, redEntries\n  - Timestamps: createdAt, ISO format\n  - If settled: closePrice, outcome, totalFee, settleTx, settledAt, verification object\n\n---\n\n### 7. Configuration — `config.ts`\n\n**Environment variables** (Close Call-specific):\n- `PYTH_BTC_USD_ACCOUNT` (line 86): Default: \"4cSM2e6rvbGQUFiJbqytoVMi5GgghSMr8LwVrT9VPSPo\"\n\n**Config type**:\n- `pythBtcUsdAccount: string` (line 20)\n\n**Loaded in config**:\n- Line 86: `pythBtcUsdAccount: process.env.PYTH_BTC_USD_ACCOUNT ?? \"4cSM2e6rvbGQUFiJbqytoVMi5GgghSMr8LwVrT9VPSPo\"`\n\n---\n\n### 8. Wiring — `index.ts`\n\n**Close Call clock initialization** (line 151-157):\n```typescript\nconst closeCallClock = createCloseCallClockWorker({\n  connection,\n  serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair,\n  pythPriceAccount: new PublicKey(config.pythBtcUsdAccount),\n});\ncloseCallClock.start();\n```\n\n**Route registration** (line 170):\n```typescript\napp.route(\"/closecall\", createCloseCallRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n**Imports**:\n- Line 12: `import { createCloseCallRoutes } from \"./routes/closecall.js\";`\n- Line 21: `import { createCloseCallClockWorker } from \"./worker/closecall-clock.js\";`\n\n---\n\n### 9. Migrations\n\n**Migration 005_closecall_rounds.sql** (line 1-27):\n\n**Table schema**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS closecall_rounds (\n  round_id       TEXT PRIMARY KEY,           -- 16-char hex (8-byte random ID)\n  pda            TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,        -- Round PDA on-chain\n  server_key     TEXT NOT NULL,               -- Server pubkey that created round\n  phase          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'open',  -- open | settled | refunded\n  open_price     BIGINT NOT NULL,             -- Pyth price at round creation\n  open_price_expo INT NOT NULL,               -- Pyth exponent\n  close_price    BIGINT,                      -- Pyth price at settlement (NULL until settled)\n  outcome        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',  -- pending | green | red | refund\n  green_pool     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,   -- Total lamports on green side\n  red_pool       BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,   -- Total lamports on red side\n  total_fee      BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,   -- Fee collected (only on decisive rounds)\n  green_entries  JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]', -- [{player, amountLamports}]\n  red_entries    JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]', -- [{player, amountLamports}]\n  settle_tx      TEXT,                        -- Settlement transaction signature\n  created_at     TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at     TIMESTAMPTZ                  -- NULL until settled/refunded\n)\n```\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_closecall_rounds_phase` on phase (for active round queries)\n- `idx_closecall_rounds_settled_at` on settled_at DESC (for history queries)\n\n---\n\n### 10. TX Builder Constants — `tx-builder.ts`\n\n**Program IDs**:\n- `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` (line 12)\n- `LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID` (line 13)\n- `CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID` (line 14) — All loaded from IDL addresses\n\n**Exported PDA deriver** (used by other code):\n- `deriveLordRoundPda(matchId)` (line 51-56): Returns [PublicKey, bump]\n\n---\n\n## Summary Statistics\n\n| Category | Count |\n|----------|-------|\n| **Close Call interfaces** | 4 (DecodedCloseCallRound, DecodedCloseCallConfig, CloseCallClockDeps, CloseCallClockWorker) |\n| **Close Call decode functions** | 3 (decodeCloseCallRound, decodeCloseCallConfig, closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter) |\n| **Close Call TX builders** | 3 (create_round, settle_round, timeout_refund) |\n| **DB methods** | 5 (insert, get by ID, get current, get history, settle) |\n| **API routes** | 2 (/current-round, /history) |\n| **Clock worker methods** | 4 (start, stop, isRunning getter, tick) |\n| **DB tables** | 1 (closecall_rounds, separate from commit-reveal `rounds`) |\n| **Migrations** | 1 (005_closecall_rounds.sql) |\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Notes\n\n1. **Separate table**: Close Call uses its own `closecall_rounds` table, not the commit-reveal `rounds` table\n2. **Clock-driven**: Settlement is time-driven (minute boundaries) via worker, not event-driven like Coinflip\n3. **Pari-mutuel pools**: Stores separate green/red entry lists with JSONB, not single-user accounts\n4. **Oracle-based**: Uses Pyth BTC/USD price feed (raw offsets at lines 33-35 of closecall-clock.ts)\n5. **Unified API**: Fairness endpoint `/by-id/:matchId` routes to correct table based on game type\n6. **Pyth integration**: Price read from on-chain account during settlement (readPythPrice function line 133-140)\n7. **Outcome determination**: Pre-determined during settlement before building TX (refund checks: empty, one-sided, single player, equal price)\n\n---\n\nAll file paths are absolute to `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a00091b546f327468 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75538\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 90718</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"efe120e9-7ceb-4e75-b227-230da807bdef","uuid":"56923f3d-2985-4d6d-a19d-a9bb81616c59","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly inventory the Close Call backend code. Search in `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/`. I need:\n\n1. Account decoders — grep for \"CloseCall\" or \"closecall\" in `worker/account-decoder.ts` — list interfaces and functions with file:line\n2. Settlement tx builders — grep for \"CloseCall\" or \"closecall\" in `worker/settle-tx.ts` — list functions with file:line\n3. Clock worker — read `worker/closecall-clock.ts` if it exists — list exports and key functions with file:line\n4. Database — grep for \"closecall\" in `db.ts` — list tables, queries, types with file:line\n5. API routes — check `routes/closecall.ts` if it exists — list routes with file:line\n6. Rounds endpoint — grep for \"closecall\" in `routes/rounds.ts` — show how it handles closecall rounds\n7. Config — grep for \"pyth\" or \"closecall\" in `config.ts`\n8. Index.ts — grep for \"closecall\" to see how it's wired up\n9. Migration files — check `migrations/` for closecall-related SQL\n\nFor each item, provide exact file:line references. Be thorough.","agentId":"a00091b546f327468","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive inventory:\n\n## Close Call Backend Code Inventory\n\n### 1. Account Decoders — `worker/account-decoder.ts`\n\n**Interfaces** (Close Call-specific):\n- `DecodedCloseCallRound` (line 125-142): Decodes on-chain CloseCallRound account with roundId, server, phase, green/red entries, pools, prices, fees\n- `DecodedCloseCallConfig` (line 144-152): Decodes CloseCallConfig with authority, treasury, pythFeedId, bettingWindowSecs, maxEntriesPerSide, paused\n\n**Functions** (Close Call):\n- `decodeCloseCallRound(data: Buffer)` (line 239-259): Returns DecodedCloseCallRound from buffer\n- `decodeCloseCallConfig(data: Buffer)` (line 261-272): Returns DecodedCloseCallConfig from buffer\n- `closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter()` (line 293-297): Returns memcmp filter for CloseCallRound account discovery\n\n**Helper enum converters** (used by decoders):\n- `closeCallPhaseToNumber(phase)` (line 50-55): Converts phase enum (Open=0, Settled=1, Refunded=2)\n- `outcomeToNumber(outcome)` (line 58-64): Converts outcome enum (Pending=0, Green=1, Red=2, Refund=3)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Settlement TX Builders — `worker/settle-tx.ts`\n\n**Instruction discriminators** (from Close Call IDL):\n- `CC_CREATE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR` (line 51)\n- `CC_SETTLE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR` (line 52)\n- `CC_TIMEOUT_REFUND_DISCRIMINATOR` (line 53)\n\n**PDA derivers**:\n- `deriveCloseCallConfigPda()` (line 524-529): Seeds: [\"closecall_config\"]\n- `deriveCloseCallRoundPda(roundId)` (line 531-536): Seeds: [\"cc_round\", roundId]\n\n**Close Call TX builders**:\n- `buildCloseCallCreateRoundTx(deps, roundId, pythPriceAccount)` (line 554-583): Builds + signs create_round instruction\n  - Keys: server (signer, writable), config (read), round (init), price_update (read), system_program\n  - Data: CC_CREATE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR + roundId (16 bytes total)\n  - Returns: {tx, roundPda}\n\n- `buildCloseCallSettleRoundTx(deps, roundId, pythPriceAccount, treasury, winnerAccounts)` (line 591-626): Builds settle_round instruction\n  - Keys: caller (signer, writable), round (writable), config, price_update, treasury, rent_receiver, ...winnerAccounts\n  - Data: CC_SETTLE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR + roundId\n  - Supports auto-payout to winners via remaining accounts\n\n- `buildCloseCallTimeoutRefundTx(deps, roundId, playerAccounts)` (line 634-665): Builds timeout_refund instruction (permissionless)\n  - Keys: caller (signer, writable), round (writable), config, rent_receiver, ...playerAccounts\n  - Refunds all players after resolve deadline\n\n**Types**:\n- `CloseCallTxDeps` (line 543-546): connection, serverKeypair\n- `CloseCallPhase` mapping: \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\"\n- `CloseCallOutcome` mapping: \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\"\n\n**Error classes**:\n- `PermanentSettleError` (line 672-677)\n- `TransientSettleError` (line 681-686)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Close Call Clock Worker — `worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n\n**Exports**:\n- `createCloseCallClockWorker(deps)` (line 70-422): Factory returning CloseCallClockWorker interface\n  \n**CloseCallClockWorker interface** (line 58-64):\n- `start()`: Discovers existing round, schedules first tick\n- `stop()`: Stops the loop\n- `isRunning`: Getter for running state\n- `tick()`: Public method for testing (runs settle + create)\n\n**Key constants**:\n- `PHASE_OPEN = 0` (line 38)\n- `TICK_OFFSET_MS = 2_000` (line 41): Runs 2s after minute boundary\n- `MAX_TX_RETRIES = 3` (line 44)\n- `TX_RETRY_DELAY_MS = 2_000` (line 45)\n\n**Pyth PriceUpdateV2 raw offsets**:\n- `PYTH_PRICE_OFFSET = 73` (line 33)\n- `PYTH_EXPO_OFFSET = 89` (line 34)\n- `PYTH_MIN_DATA_LEN = 93` (line 35)\n\n**Internal tick logic**:\n- `settlePreviousRound()` (line 198-308): Settlement flow with outcome pre-determination\n  - Determines refund condition: empty entries, one-sided, single player, or equal price\n  - Selects winner accounts based on price comparison\n  - Calls `buildCloseCallSettleRoundTx` with appropriate winner list\n  - Logs settle attempts with retry on failure\n\n- `createNewRound()` (line 314-340): Creates new round at minute boundary\n  - Generates random 8-byte roundId\n  - Calls `buildCloseCallCreateRoundTx`\n  - Updates in-memory active round tracking\n\n- `tick()` (line 346-357): Main loop operation\n  - Step 1: Settle previous round\n  - Step 2: Create new round\n\n- `discoverActiveRound()` (line 157-188): On startup, scans for existing Open round owned by server\n  - Uses `closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter()` to find rounds\n  - Recovers in-memory state from on-chain account\n\n---\n\n### 4. Database — `db.ts`\n\n**Types** (Close Call-specific):\n- `CloseCallPhase = \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\"` (line 16)\n- `CloseCallOutcome = \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\"` (line 17)\n- `CloseCallRound` interface (line 19-36): round_id, pda, server_key, phase, open_price, open_price_expo, close_price, outcome, green_pool, red_pool, total_fee, green_entries, red_entries, settle_tx, created_at, settled_at\n- `InsertCloseCallRoundParams` (line 38-44): roundId, pda, serverKey, openPrice, openPriceExpo\n\n**Db interface methods** (Close Call):\n- `insertCloseCallRound(params)` (line 171): Returns CloseCallRound\n- `getCloseCallRound(roundId)` (line 174): By 16-char hex roundId\n- `getCloseCallCurrentRound()` (line 177): Returns current open round or undefined\n- `getCloseCallHistory(limit)` (line 180): Returns last N settled/refunded rounds\n- `settleCloseCallRound(roundId, updates)` (line 183-196): Updates phase, outcome, closePrice, pools, fees, entries, settleTx\n\n**Implementation** (createDb):\n- `insertCloseCallRound` (line 353-366): INSERT into closecall_rounds table\n- `getCloseCallRound` (line 368-373): SELECT by round_id\n- `getCloseCallCurrentRound` (line 375-383): SELECT WHERE phase='open' ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 1\n- `getCloseCallHistory` (l